service: Welcome to the AWS Ground Station API Reference. AWS Ground Station is a fully managed service that enables you to control satellite communications, downlink and process satellite data, and scale your satellite operations efficiently and cost-effectively without having to build or manage your own ground station infrastructure.

operations.CancelContact: Cancels a contact with a specified contact ID.
operations.CreateConfig:
Creates a Config with the specified configData parameters.

Only one type of configData can be specified.
operations.CreateDataflowEndpointGroup:
Creates a DataflowEndpoint group containing the specified list of DataflowEndpoint objects.

The name field in each endpoint is used in your mission profile DataflowEndpointConfig to specify which endpoints to use during a contact.

When a contact uses multiple DataflowEndpointConfig objects, each Config must match a DataflowEndpoint in the same group.
operations.CreateMissionProfile:
Creates a mission profile.

dataflowEdges is a list of lists of strings. Each lower level list of strings has two elements: a from ARN and a to ARN.
operations.GetConfig:
Returns Config information.

Only one Config response can be returned.
operations.GetMinuteUsage: Returns the number of minutes used by account.
operations.ListContacts:
Returns a list of contacts.

If statusList contains AVAILABLE, the request must include groundStation, missionprofileArn, and satelliteArn.
operations.ListTagsForResource: Returns a list of tags for a specified resource.
operations.UpdateConfig:
Updates the Config used when scheduling contacts.

Updating a Config will not update the execution parameters for existing future contacts scheduled with this Config.
operations.UpdateMissionProfile:
Updates a mission profile.

Updating a mission profile will not update the execution parameters for existing future contacts.

refs.Destination$configDetails: Additional details for a Config, if type is dataflow endpoint or antenna demod decode.
refs.Source$configDetails: Additional details for a Config, if type is dataflow endpoint or antenna demod decode.

ConfigTypeData.base:

DataflowDetail.base: Information about a dataflow edge used in a contact.

refs.CreateMissionProfileRequest$dataflowEdge: A list of lists of ARNs. Each list of ARNs is an edge, with a from Config and a to Config.
refs.GetMissionProfileResponse$dataflowEdges: A list of lists of ARNs. Each list of ARNs is an edge, with a from Config and a to Config.
refs.UpdateMissionProfileRequest$dataflowEdge: A list of lists of ARNs. Each list of ARNs is an edge, with a from Config and a to Config.

refs.DataflowEndpoint$mtu: Maximum transmission unit (MTU) size in bytes of a dataflow endpoint.

refs.Eirp$value: Value of an EIRP. Valid values are between 20.0 to 50.0 dBW.
refs.Frequency$value: Frequency value. Valid values are between 2200 to 2300 MHz and 7750 to 8400 MHz for downlink and 2025 to 2120 MHz for uplink.
refs.FrequencyBandwidth$value:
Frequency bandwidth value. AWS Ground Station currently has the following bandwidth limitations:

  • For AntennaDownlinkDemodDecodeconfig, valid values are between 125 kHz to 650 MHz.

  • For AntennaDownlinkconfig, valid values are between 10 kHz to 54 MHz.

  • For AntennaUplinkConfig, valid values are between 10 kHz to 54 MHz.

refs.CreateMissionProfileRequest$contactPostP: Amount of time after a contact ends that you’d like to receive a CloudWatch event indicating the pass has finished.
refs.CreateMissionProfileRequest$contactPrePa: Amount of time prior to contact start you’d like to receive a CloudWatch event indicating an upcoming pass.
refs.CreateMissionProfileRequest$minimumViabl: Smallest amount of time in seconds that you’d like to see for an available contact. AWS Ground Station will not present you with contacts shorter than this duration.
refs.GetMissionProfileResponse$contactPostPas: Amount of time after a contact ends that you’d like to receive a CloudWatch event indicating the pass has finished.
refs.GetMissionProfileResponse$contactPrePass: Amount of time prior to contact start you’d like to receive a CloudWatch event indicating an upcoming pass.
refs.GetMissionProfileResponse$minimumViableC: Smallest amount of time in seconds that you’d like to see for an available contact. AWS Ground Station will not present you with contacts shorter than this duration.
refs.UpdateMissionProfileRequest$contactPostP: Amount of time after a contact ends that you’d like to receive a CloudWatch event indicating the pass has finished.
refs.UpdateMissionProfileRequest$contactPrePa: Amount of time after a contact ends that you’d like to receive a CloudWatch event indicating the pass has finished.
refs.UpdateMissionProfileRequest$minimumViabl: Smallest amount of time in seconds that you’d like to see for an available contact. AWS Ground Station will not present you with contacts shorter than this duration.

Elevation.base: Elevation angle of the satellite in the sky during a contact.

refs.CreateDataflowEndpointGroupRequest$endpo: Endpoint details of each endpoint in the dataflow endpoint group.

refs.SpectrumConfig$centerFrequency: Center frequency of a spectral Config. Valid values are between 2200 to 2300 MHz and 7750 to 8400 MHz for downlink and 2025 to 2120 MHz for uplink.
refs.UplinkSpectrumConfig$centerFrequency: Center frequency of an uplink spectral Config. Valid values are between 2025 to 2120 MHz.

refs.SpectrumConfig$bandwidth:
Bandwidth of a spectral Config. AWS Ground Station currently has the following bandwidth limitations:

  • For AntennaDownlinkDemodDecodeconfig, valid values are between 125 kHz to 650 MHz.

  • For AntennaDownlinkconfig valid values are between 10 kHz to 54 MHz.

  • For AntennaUplinkConfig, valid values are between 10 kHz to 54 MHz.

refs.SatelliteListItem$groundStations: A list of ground stations to which the satellite is on-boarded.
